ident\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 356}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 369}, {\"ngram\": \"Organising Committee\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 395}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic torch\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 423}, {\"ngram\": \"the Panathenaic Stadium\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 450}, {\"ngram\": \"Athens\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 460}, {\"ngram\": \"The event\", \"from\": 461, \"to\": 470}, {\"ngram\": \"the iconic Panathenaic Stadium\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 526}, {\"ngram\": \"the relay's transition\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 647}, {\"ngram\": \"the flame\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 664}, {\"ngram\": \"a voyage\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 700}, {\"ngram\": \"the Mediterranean\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 725}, {\"ngram\": \"President\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"a moving speech\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 900}, {\"ngram\": \"his fellow citizens\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"the warm welcome\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"the flame\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 971}, {\"ngram\": \"its national relay\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1006}, {\"ngram\": \"his best wishes\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1031}, {\"ngram\": \"the torch embarks\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"its \\\"next journey\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1084}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"\\\"Today, in a crowded Panathenaic stadium, a unique journey of hope and pride that has illuminated the whole of Greece from one end to the other comes to its end.\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panathenaic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Panathenaic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panathenaic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panathenaic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1197, \"end\": 1203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999999802043933, \"rank\": 1.0611729943837551e-08, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a unique journey\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1144}, {\"ngram\": \"hope\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1152}, {\"ngram\": \"pride\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1162}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1193}, {\"ngram\": \"one end\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1216}, {\"ngram\": \"its end\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1246}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And yet these 11 days that have captivated our country and captured the attention of the whole world are just the beginning of a great journey.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1391, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these 11 days\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1269}, {\"ngram\": \"our country\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1302}, {\"ngram\": \"the attention\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1329}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole world\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1348}, {\"ngram\": \"just the beginning\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1371}, {\"ngram\": \"a great journey\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That of the next Olympic Games in Paris 2024,\\\" the Olympic's official website quoted Capralos as saying.\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1426, \"end\": 1436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999918145, \"rank\": 8.15929760679469e-12, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1422}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic's official website\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"Capralos\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1485}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is therefore with great joy and emotion that we all welcome the Olympic flame together here at the Panathenaic Stadium at the end of the torch relay on Greek soil, to hand it over to the Paris 2024 Organising Committee with a feeling of respect and solidarity, but also accompanied by our best wishes for the realisation of a unique event,\\\" he added.After thereafter, Tony Estanguet (FRA), the President of the Paris 2024 Organizing Committee, gave a speech in which he expressed gratitude to the Greek people for organizing both the flame lighting and handover ceremonies, as well as to Papadakis and Hess, the two French torchbearers of the handover event.\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 2158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9983369434775062, \"rank\": 0.001580136328480174, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1868, \"end\": 1882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 1997, \"end\": 2009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9987141677906048, \"rank\": 0.0012874877024887862, \"text\": \"Greek people\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 2088, \"end\": 2097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriella_Papadakis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Papadakis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriella_Papadakis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriella_Papadakis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngr